original_title: Alaska’s State Parks: The Last Frontier
overview: Sprawling across 1.6 million acres of wilderness, Wood-Tikchik is one of the largest state parks in the United States (around the same size as Delaware). Chugach, on the other hand, is an easily reachable state park just miles from downtown Anchorage. Both parks (and their can't-miss sights) are covered here.
title: Alaska’s State Parks: The Last Frontier
